race.comment: CHICO CASINO (3) has been just behind the placegetters at both runs this prep, most recently finishing 1.7 lengths away after leading over this distance at Cowra. Cherry ripe now and from the good gate will be prominent from the outset. MY CROWN (16) found 900m too short when resuming at Gunnedah recently but he was strong late. Raced once at this trip for a win so he can progress off that last run. TWIN GIFT (14) went back to last from a wide gate then picked up nicely to pass half the field in a respectable effort over this distance at Cowra last time. Can race closer today and is not out of contention. KOBOLD (9) resumes. Opened last prep with a minor placing at Wellington. Best form comes at 1200m so she cannot be dismissed. RIVER ROGUE (6) was well held when resuming last start but will find this a more suitable assignment.
